				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can verify that DOT damage disrupts spellcasting from personal experience. I got a DOT cast on me, and I couldn't get a spell off because the damage ticks would interrupt my casting every time. Knowing this gives mentalists a lot more kick in RVR, in that we are capable of totally shutting down opposing casters for as long as our DOTs will hold. Imagine this little scenario...
<br />

<br />
1. A general advance is made to get into casting range, under covering fire from our casters, rangers, etc.
<br />
2. Our Mentalists DOT the enemy casters.
<br />
3. Our side makes a concerted charge. Enemy casters can't nuke because of the DOT damage.
<br />
4. Our big melees and nasty nukers clean house while the Mentalists heal.
<br />

<br />
An ideal scenario certainly, but it gets the idea across.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
