				<td valign="top" align="right" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=20635&amp;sid=0d1d8995838589bee9db6150d93f9fc0"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">OK, if anyone from Mythic ever reads these boards.... 
<br />

<br />
Mentalists DO need some major changes made to be anything near effective in RvR. I request 3 "small" changes, one for each spec.
<br />

<br />

<br />
1- Make the Heal over time line of spells cure rez sickness. Right now its primary use is to get recently rezzed tanks back in the fight. Well they don't usually do that till rez sickness goes away. At least give the higher level spells this effect.
<br />

<br />
2- Change charm. The way it is works sort of fine in PvE, but is worthless in RvR. The main thing is finding mobs, But even if you do you probably can't charm them. So currently on a L50, 100% light spec mentalist could do anything other than heal.
<br />

<br />
3. increase the range on the mana spec dot spell line and the light based DD line by double. I picked the spec lines so that people who haven't put points into the line don't gain benefit. But as it stands we can't use these spells very effectively in combat at all. By the time we're close enough to use them we're dead. Every other caster does more damage, has a greater range, or has some way of protecting themselves while they cast (pet etc). 
<br />

<br />
Other suggestions... 
<br />

<br />
- an invis spell line
<br />
- Allow charm vs other realm players
<br />
- allow the confusion lines to work on RvR (haven't been able to use this yet, short range and it longish cast time.
<br />

<br />
To keep PvE in balance, make the range of our spells doubled vs humanoids. We are mentalists, we would be more effective vs humans than say against cats and dogs.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
